# 🧭 Application Creation Guide

This guide explains how to **create an application** and **set up application variables** in the platform.  
All images are embedded directly in this file using Base64 encoding, so there is no need for external hosting.

---

## 🧱 Step 1: Selecting an Application

When you log in, you will see the initial interface as shown below.  
You can select between the existing applications. By default, the system provides:

- **system** *(should not be modified unless you know what you are doing)*  
- **demo** *(contains example endpoints for each handler)*

  <figcaption>Application selection screen</figcaption>
</figure>


---

## 🆕 Step 2: Creating a New Application

An application allows you to **group related endpoints** under a single logical entity.  
For example, you can create an application named `pizzeria` and include all endpoints related to the pizza business.

**Important best practices when naming applications:**
- Use only **lowercase letters**.
- Do **not** use spaces or special characters.
- Follow URL-safe naming conventions.

To create a new application:
1. Click on the **“NEW APP”** button.
2. Fill in the application name.
3. (Optional) Enable or disable the application using the **“ENABLE”** toggle.
4. Add a clear and descriptive **description** explaining the purpose of the application.


<figure>
  <img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="New Application form" />
  <figcaption>New Application form</figcaption>
</figure>


---

## 🧭 Step 3: Application Variables

Under the **“Application Variables”** tab, you can define variables for the three available environments:
- DEVELOPMENT
- QUALITY
- PRODUCTION

These variables allow you to store reusable values that can be accessed by any endpoint within the application.


<figure>
  <img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="Application Variables screen" />
  <figcaption>Application Variables screen</figcaption>
</figure>


---

## ✍️ Step 4: Creating an Application Variable

To create a variable:

1. Enter the variable name in **UPPERCASE**, without spaces or special characters.
2. Click **“NEW”**.
3. A small editor will appear where you can assign a value to the variable.  
   - Supported types: `string`, `JSON`, or `numeric`.
4. You can **show or hide** the value by clicking the eye icon.
5. Finally, click **“SAVE & DEPLOY”** to save and activate the application.


<figure>
  <img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="Creating and editing an application variable" />
  <figcaption>Creating and editing an application variable</figcaption>
</figure>


---

## 📝 Best Practices

- Always use **clear and descriptive names** for both applications and variables.  
- Group endpoints logically to keep the system clean and organized.  
- Keep sensitive values stored in application variables rather than hardcoding them.  
- Remember to deploy changes after modifying variables.

---

## ✅ Summary

- Applications group related endpoints.  
- Variables can be set per environment.  
- All naming should follow lowercase and URL-safe conventions.  
- After configuration, use **Save & Deploy** to make the application available.
